trans-unit.source: Provides programmatic access to the HTML `head` element in server code.
The HTML `head` element is a container that can contain additional information about the page.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlHead> control is useful for specifying page formatting information that can be accessed at run time.
Adding styles or style rules programmatically during asynchronous postbacks is not supported.
When you add AJAX capabilities to an ASP.NET Web page, asynchronous postbacks update regions of the page without updating the whole page.
For more information, see [Microsoft Ajax Overview](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/be84d9b3-b7cd-47d7-8494-be4abfaad9cb).
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlHead"></xref> class.
The following table shows the initial property value for an instance of <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlHead>.
Property
Initial value
The string "head".
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlHead"></xref> class by using the specified tag.
The following table shows the initial property value for an instance of <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlHead>.
Property
Initial value
The value of the `tag` parameter.
A string that specifies the tag name of the control.
Gets the content of the "description" `meta` element.
For information about this property, see the <xref:System.Web.UI.Page.MetaDescription%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property.
The content of the "description" `meta` element.
Gets the content of the "keywords" `meta` element.
For information about this property, see the <xref:System.Web.UI.Page.MetaKeywords%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property.
The content of the "keywords" `meta` element.
Gets an <xref href="System.Web.UI.IStyleSheet"></xref> instance that represents the style rules in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlHead"></xref> control.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlHead.StyleSheet%2A> property returns an <xref:System.Web.UI.IStyleSheet> that represents the embedded style rules in the <xref:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlHead> control.
Adding styles or style rules programmatically during asynchronous postbacks is not supported.
When you add AJAX capabilities to an ASP.NET Web page, asynchronous postbacks update regions of the page without updating the whole page.
For more information, see [Microsoft Ajax Overview](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/be84d9b3-b7cd-47d7-8494-be4abfaad9cb).
An object that represents the style rules in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlHead"></xref> control.
Gets the page title.
The page title.
